Recently I was able to finally check a visit to the Empire State Building off my NYC bucket list! Thank you to the team over at @empirestatebldg for showing me a great time.
.
If you haven’t been, there are newly renovated exhibits on the 2nd floor along with incredible viewpoints on the 86th and 102nd floor observatories. As if that wasn’t enough, they’ve also just opened the 80th floor for even more exhibits and views of NYC. I’ve posted a short series in my story, check ‘em out.

A November sunset to remember down 6th Avenue last night. 🌇
A New York fall meets a New York winter and an ice skater getting the best of both worlds. 🍂❄️
Colorful sidewalks and warm(ish) morning sun in the upper west side. Fall vibes will not stop until I see snow! 😛
Fall is quickly coming to an end, so I decided to get one last view of the remaining color overlooking Columbus Circle. 🍂
Fiery skies over the Brooklyn Bridge. I don’t think this icon has a single bad angle, do you?
A fall oasis hidden amongst the concrete of Brooklyn. Love finding little gems like this around the city. 🍁

Central Park is full of pretty bridges, but the Gothic Bridge, pictured here wrapped in a beautiful autumn coat, may be my favorite.
Fall continues to be my favorite time of year in NYC. Do you guys have a favorite season where you live? 🍁
Consider this your warning, pumpkins will continue to be featured in this feed until Dec 1. Someone needs to stand up to Santa. 🤓

That feeling when you find complementary colors in the wild. 😍
A rare same day shot & post for me; this was taken during my morning stroll around Brooklyn Heights today.

Early mornings are really the ideal time to take in Bethesda Fountain. You have the benefit of not only being one of the few people there, but more importantly the light that dances through the water is absolutely gorgeous.
Everybody loves a New York City fall 🍂
Early November means the fall foliage party is in full swing in NYC! Only trouble is deciding where to go. 🍁
Spooktober coming to an end, had to give it a proper send-off. Happy Halloween! 🕸🎃
Catching some rays from the Manhattan Bridge walkway. Easily one of my favorite views of this city.
Sunset walks along the Brooklyn waterfront in Dumbo. Saw this “S” curve from above surrounded by fall colors & covered in light and I could not take me eyes off it.
